      "span_text": "Four other oviducts were each mounted between a slide and coverslip, slightly compressed and examined for the behaviour of spermatozoa within the oviduct by viewing them through the oviducal wall  Number of spermatozoa remaining in the isthmus after flushing in situ Neither the volume of flushing medium (30, 90, 180 pi) nor the time of flushing (3 or 6 h after mating) had a significant effect on the percentage of spermatozoa remaining in the caudal isthmus ( Table 2) ."
